Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.60,0:52:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then feeds
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.60,0:52:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.60,0:52:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and anger
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.60,0:52:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and blows
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.60,0:52:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,away
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.60,0:52:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,slides
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.66,0:52:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.66,0:52:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.66,0:52:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,want you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.66,0:52:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.66,0:52:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.66,0:52:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,hate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.66,0:52:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.14,0:52:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you find
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.14,0:52:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.14,0:52:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,saying
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.14,0:52:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.14,0:52:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.14,0:52:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the same
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.14,0:52:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.14,0:52:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.14,0:52:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,can't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.14,0:52:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,change
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.14,0:52:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.90,0:52:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,model
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.58,0:52:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.14,0:52:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.14,0:52:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,character.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.14,0:52:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.18,0:52:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.18,0:52:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,like
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.18,0:52:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.18,0:52:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,1992
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.18,0:52:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Pixar
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.18,0:52:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.18,0:52:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.18,0:52:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,catch
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.18,0:52:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.18,0:52:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,saying
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.18,0:52:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.18,0:52:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.18,0:52:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.18,0:52:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,want to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.18,0:52:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,look at
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.18,0:53:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate the color green.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.48,0:53:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't really hate the color green.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.46,0:53:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick that up in kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.14,0:53:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kindergarten is where you learn all the hate words.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.90,0:53:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate pigtails.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.10,0:53:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.86,0:53:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.58,0:53:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.24,0:53:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.69,0:53:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate apples.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.89,0:53:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate applesauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.57,0:53:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate Wheaties.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.41,0:53:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate vitamin pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.87,0:53:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things you hate when you're a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.69,0:53:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The kindergarten is full of things you hate
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.67,0:53:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and kids you hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.75,0:53:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So humor, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.75,0:53:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when you say I hate something,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.99,0:53:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you catch that that is a style of languaging
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.63,0:53:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that you picked up from kindergarten
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.23,0:53:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you try to let it go
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.47,0:53:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by seeing people differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.99,0:53:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to feel guilty about character defects
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.95,0:53:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are characteristic of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.57,0:53:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't want to fall then into self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.96,0:54:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hate myself for hating.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.56,0:54:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate myself for hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.79,0:54:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hate hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.49,0:54:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate myself for hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.61,0:54:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people who hate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.94,0:54:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you sink into the merry-go-round of hating this
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.82,0:54:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and hating yourself for hating this
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.72,0:54:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the only way out of it is to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.24,0:54:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.88,0:54:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you just say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.42,0:54:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.78,0:54:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody raised their hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.80,0:54:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, they were just praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.70,0:54:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.16,0:54:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory, hallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.02,0:54:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.40,0:54:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Resentments, people who are in 12-step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.68,0:54:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,know that resentment is the one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.78,0:54:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that trips up more people than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.12,0:54:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no, I like the saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.12,0:54:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no such thing as a justified resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.56,0:54:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.01,0:54:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.59,0:54:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to accept God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.39,0:54:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,means to accept the karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.93,0:54:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that go with existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.47,0:54:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.25,0:55:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmic consequences that go with existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.67,0:55:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.91,0:55:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.97,0:55:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.33,0:55:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.35,0:55:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.37,0:55:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.39,0:55:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.49,0:55:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.53,0:55:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmic consequences that go with existence
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.81,0:55:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is just protoplasmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.31,0:55:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Protoplasmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.53,0:55:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this body is protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.27,0:55:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you hang out with protoplasm long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.99,0:55:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.48,0:55:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you see better with a magnifying glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.41,0:55:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The karma of protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.70,0:55:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So resentment then is,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.56,0:55:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it tends to smolder
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.02,0:55:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to recontextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.32,0:55:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, those of you who do the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.90,0:55:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know that what you're asking for
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.40,0:55:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Holy Spirit to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.56,0:55:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualize it so you see it differently. When you see it differently, it's taken out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.07,0:55:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of time and location and the causality that you associate with it. When you see it outside
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.25,0:55:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of time and outside of causality, you see it's nothing but a phenomena. Because with
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.72,0:56:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced consciousness, all you see is phenomena, constant shifting of phenomena. The world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.16,0:56:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is phenomenologic as far as perception goes. Things are always changing, appearing to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.24,0:56:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually they're just transforming into their own, the actualization of their own potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.02,0:56:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How to let go of resentments, the classic way of course is through forgiveness. And
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.09,0:56:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can even get car insurance now that includes forgiveness. What's that company? They forgive
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.34,0:56:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you one accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.34,0:56:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The big black guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.24,0:56:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The big black guy with a great voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.24,0:56:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Allstate.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.72,0:56:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Allstate, yeah. He's got a great voice. I love his voice. Every time he comes on, you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.10,0:56:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,know, he's got just a magnificent voice. Forgiveness, you know, accident forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.68,0:56:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time he says that, I think, isn't that wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.16,0:57:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you have to do is become spiritually an Allstater and be willing to forgive people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.41,0:57:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.91,0:57:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.91,0:57:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They said something you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.31,0:57:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They did something you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.07,0:57:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They believe in a politician you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.25,0:57:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to be willing to be at least up to the level of Allstate.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.64,0:57:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here willing to be forgiving of the next accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.76,0:57:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody holding out against Allstate?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.98,0:57:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so when you get honest with yourself, strict honesty, this is sort of a style of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.57,0:57:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,self-examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.89,0:57:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Strict honesty means that you confront yourself with the juice you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.89,0:57:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.89,0:57:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.89,0:57:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to get away with the juice you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.61,0:57:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling right and feeling righteous and you're juicing the resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.39,0:57:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the basis of the ego, as we've said over and over, is the juice that it gets out of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.37,0:58:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.84,0:58:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up the positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.08,0:58:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You only have to be willing to surrender the juice that you get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.08,0:58:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you let go of the juice you get out of it, then the positionality drops of its
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.26,0:58:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,own.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.64,0:58:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If an investment doesn't pay any interest anymore, you don't cling to it tenaciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.94,0:58:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You look for someplace else to put your money, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.10,0:58:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So when resentment no longer pays off, no matter what ego problem you're dealing with,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.03,0:58:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're always dealing with the narcissistic satisfaction that is being gotten out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.71,0:58:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the political world of today, you see how everybody loves making somebody else
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.27,0:58:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.27,0:58:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You just see the glee.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.87,0:58:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The glee is the ego juice, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.97,0:58:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can find your competitor into something horrific, people just crow with glee.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.27,0:59:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.27,0:59:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They just crow with the glee of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.65,0:59:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They just love it to find something wrong in the opposition party.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.45,0:59:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.45,0:59:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're like piranhas.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.65,0:59:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so eager for it, they jump it and over-inflate it and exaggerate it, trying
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.67,0:59:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to juice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.67,0:59:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They use it for every piece of juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.11,0:59:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only thing to let go of a positionality is not the positionality itself, but the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.79,0:59:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender the juice that you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.76,0:59:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can put it up on your bulletin board.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.26,0:59:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the juice I'm getting out of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.44,0:59:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the juice?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.27,0:59:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And is the juice worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.01,0:59:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes probably the juice does seem like it's worth it, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.21,0:59:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then you don't get enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.21,0:59:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.21,0:59:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't everybody get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.46,0:59:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, yeah, if you get too crowded there, all them enlightened beings running all over
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.09,1:00:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the planet at one time, the grass would, I don't know if things would even grow with
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.94,1:00:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all that kind of energy around it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.22,1:00:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So malice and jealousy, envy, these all go together, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.42,1:00:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanity and, these are all merely ways of pridefulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.44,1:00:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How to get over craving and greed, wanting and desire?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.10,1:00:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are some difficult ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.12,1:00:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the juice that you get out of the negative is why you hang on to the negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.19,1:00:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What about craving this and wanting this?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.27,1:00:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're happy to the degree that your halves meet your wants.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.20,1:00:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want practically nothing in the world, you're happy all the time because there's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.08,1:00:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing here you're lacking.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.86,1:00:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody to be mad at.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.66,1:00:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go of wanting this, then, and letting go of desires?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.54,1:00:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,One.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.54,1:01:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that most ambitions and desires are not so much for the thing itself, but for the glamour of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.34,1:01:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the media have exaggerated the glamour of everything. You watch shows on television,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.52,1:01:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they're nothing but superficial glamour. There's absolutely no substance to them. The people have no substance. They stand for nothing of any substance.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.24,1:01:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is only about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.44,1:01:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,transitory appearance, a transitory appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.92,1:01:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You say you're a big star at a certain thing, and then if you don't match the transitory appearance demands of the media,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.42,1:01:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're nobody. So you never were anybody, I guess, because you were just an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.39,1:01:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A saleable appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.95,1:01:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.59,1:01:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the less you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.82,1:01:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,want,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.92,1:01:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the less you end up needing, and then finally you realize that it really takes nothing to make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.98,1:01:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that you need comes to you. Everything you need comes to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.72,1:01:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.47,1:01:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,either that or Walmart says it, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.19,1:02:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, these are Dr. Scholl's shoes, and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.15,1:02:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they're pretty kind. This jacket was a present from a friend of mine. Where'd you get your outfit?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.81,1:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She got it at Goodwill. We do our shopping at Goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.02,1:02:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth. She got it at Goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.35,1:02:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see how easy it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.87,1:02:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How easy it is. Dr. Scholl's shoes get you closer to Goodwill. So what do you need, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.13,1:02:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's no disparity between what you want and what you have, then you're happy all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.41,1:03:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Unhappiness is wanting something, desiring something, that's out there instead of seeing that what you have already satisfactory.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.03,1:03:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to improve something? Yes, there's nothing wrong with that. That's aesthetics, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.93,1:03:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.15,1:03:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetics, you comb your hair and you try to look nice, that's aesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.43,1:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetics is you try to bring forth the beauty of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.49,1:03:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So to improve life to me is to improve its beauty in certain ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.70,1:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a new thing in your bathroom so that it looks more beautiful and is more handy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.14,1:03:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But your happiness doesn't depend on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.68,1:03:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more your satisfaction with the aesthetics of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.40,1:03:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You become more aware of aesthetics and the intrinsic beauty of all things.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.50,1:03:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you stop craving things and greed disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.44,1:03:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And wantingness disappears and desiringness disappears
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.42,1:03:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's an inner satisfaction with everything just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.12,1:04:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything stayed just exactly the way it is this moment, would it be okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.98,1:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Freeze. Freeze frame. Freeze frame. Freeze frame okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.71,1:04:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Freeze frame. Any objections?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.82,1:04:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wants to change the world today?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.62,1:04:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have been at these lectures before.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.48,1:04:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All the world changers.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.88,1:04:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.02,1:04:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, of greater assistance is to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.54,1:04:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that life is evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.52,1:04:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is not causal. It's evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.84,1:04:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.46,1:04:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That creation and evolution are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.24,1:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that everything has an inherent limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.54,1:04:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.06,1:04:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A duck cannot be a cat.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.32,1:04:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.12,1:04:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender to what the available options are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.30,1:04:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to finish this chart and then we'll take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.24,1:04:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to finish this chart and then we'll take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.50,1:05:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to finish this chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.86,1:05:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Choices depend on situations and karmic proclivities.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.41,1:05:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the karmic consequences, karmic consequences, is that we are as humans stuck with the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.85,1:05:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the problems that automatically come with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.93,1:05:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We automatically go with having an ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.07,1:05:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could get a resentment about that, except we say,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.69,1:05:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that's the price of the gift of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.19,1:05:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather be alive and working on the inherent problems intrinsic to being human than dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.73,1:05:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be thankful for life, to see the world as an evolving creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.76,1:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to accept that your time here is limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.52,1:05:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You accept the earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.32,1:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The earlier in life you accept mortality, the better.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.62,1:06:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of all the psychological fears, at the bottom of all the piles is the fear of death itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.54,1:06:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get over that one, nobody can really do anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.48,1:06:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.16,1:06:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy says, I'm going to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.52,1:06:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's your problem, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.84,1:06:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.44,1:06:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his goddamn problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.90,1:06:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.34,1:06:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.36,1:06:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.28,1:06:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So he gets that you picture it that it's his problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.94,1:06:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can walk right through all kinds of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.48,1:06:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've told you some of the things I've walked through.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.52,1:06:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.59,1:06:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull the trigger, it's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.21,1:06:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't give a damn.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.92,1:06:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've got to mean that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.38,1:06:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't try it if you didn't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.33,1:06:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll say, oh, yeah, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.19,1:06:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Boing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.71,1:06:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.99,1:06:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.72,1:06:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic and hidden beneath.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.60,1:06:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic is the exquisite beauty and perfection of God's love,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.14,1:06:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which expresses itself as mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.47,1:07:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is merciful is probably the mercifulness of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.20,1:07:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the most difficult of all things to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.78,1:07:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty of life you eventually see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.52,1:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfection of all of life you eventually see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.60,1:07:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mercy of all of life, that's the hard one to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.49,1:07:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That intrinsic to what you see is disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.43,1:07:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's divine mercy, allowing you the grace of undoing that negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.45,1:07:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which would have put you into hell, and you have now undone it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.59,1:07:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, oh, Lord, for my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.69,1:07:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Through human life, we reach salvation through the undoing of negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.25,1:07:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the adoption of positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.19,1:07:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one way of putting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.73,1:07:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, human life is an expression of divine grace,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.04,1:07:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,grace and infinite mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.72,1:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take a break there.
